spans.text: On Learning's wing we pierce empyreal sky
the gloom of solitude's lone hour
less , with gratitude refined , Shall my warm heart your honoured partner share
how great , how good his mind
a guilty race , The dread , tremendous word
Death , masked , oft shares the ball and festive bower , And beckons , unawares , the soul away
Sad comforts ! where their poor expedients
what pleased guide shall waft the trembler home
Sad comforts ! where their poor expedients
do thy terrors round me wait
Over peopled orbs it wanders unconfined
a state serene , But melts , distressed by Pity's soft commands
with pale Misery to the dreary shade
, will you scorn the poor unpolished Muse
my once cheerless soul to views sublime
Pour down , great God ! thy choicest blessings here , Such virtues merit thy peculiar love ; OH !
their beauteous progeny thy care , And lift them
